p: Online survey respondents closely resembled the target audience for the study materials due to inclusion criteria (Table 3). The highest level of education completed by this sample was some college (or a 2-year degree) (76.7 %). The majority of respondents (64.4 %) had an income between $31,000 and $40,000 per year. The remainder of the sample had lower levels of education or lower income. Over one-quarter of the sample was Black (28.8 %) and a similar proportion was White (27.1 %). Hispanic respondents comprised 17.8 % of the sample. Most respondents were between 25 and 44 years old (73.3 %). The sample was mostly female (71.9 %).
